# Levels & Asset Loading

## Principles

- **Levels are a scene specialization** — a level is always loaded as a scene; not every scene is a level
- **Catalog / local store is cheap; scenes are ephemeral** — level documents stay in localStorage; each `switchTo` creates a new `Scene` and destroys the previous
- **Only the active level owns runtime state** — one scene registry, one nav grid, one set of entities at a time
- **Parsed assets are cached; GL meshes are not** — `GltfCache` dedupes fetch/parse by URL across level visits; each spawn still builds its own GPU meshes
- **Transitions are async** — preload assets, then `load()`; gate input with `switching`

## Portable vs authoring shapes

| Shape | Package | Contents |
|-------|---------|----------|
| `LevelDefinition` | `viberanium/definitions/levels/` | Indexed `simpleProps` / `standardProps` / `simpleActors` / `standardActors` + composition props/actors/colliders + `playerSpawn`. No `aiPackage`, groups, parse/serialize |
| `LevelDocument` / `.level` | Construct `catalog/levels/` | `version: 1`, same index/composition (plus collider instances + player spawn), instance names, actor `aiPackage`, groups |
| `levelFile` parse | Sandbox `catalog/levels/levelFile.ts` | Parses the same JSON → portable `LevelDefinition` + `aiPackages` map (ignores groups at runtime) |

Index entries are unique; composition instances reference `indexId` + kind. Shared localStorage key: `construct.levelLocalStore`.

## Layout

```
viberanium/src/
  definitions/levels/   LevelDefinition, collectUrlsFromLevel, resolveLevel*
  spawn/instantiateProp.ts

sandbox/src/catalog/levels/
  levelDefinition.ts    re-export portable types
  levelFile.ts          parse .level JSON
  levelSeed.ts          seed documents for first boot
  helpers.ts            placement builders
  testOne.ts …          indexed LevelBuild seeds
  registry.ts           LEVEL_SEED_DOCUMENTS
  collectAssetUrls.ts   wraps collectUrlsFromLevel

sandbox/src/storage/levelLocalStore.ts
sandbox/src/menus/levels/LevelSelectModal.tsx
sandbox/src/globals/sceneManager.ts   switchTo + Digit0 → UI callback; Digit1–4 → test seeds
sandbox/src/scenes/common/
  createPlayableScene.ts
  useLevelScene.ts      resolve index → instantiateProp / spawnActor
  prop.ts               re-export instantiateProp from viberanium
```

## Session flow

```
Digit0 → LevelSelectModal (list local store + multi-import .level)
Digit1–4 → switchTo(testOne|testTwo|testThree|testFour)
  → switchTo(levelId)
  → game.setActiveScene(null)        // sync unload; drop previous Scene
  → gltfCache.preload(collectUrlsFromLevel(def))
  → scene = useLevelScene(deps, def, aiPackages)  // NEW registry
  → game.setActiveScene(scene)
  → await scene.load()
```

Bootstrap seeds `construct.levelLocalStore` from `LEVEL_SEED_DOCUMENTS` when empty, then `switchTo` the first available id.

## load() / unload()

| Phase | Creates / destroys |
|-------|--------------------|
| `load()` | nav grid, ground, props + level colliders from index, actors from index (+ `testAi` when aiPackage), player at `playerSpawn` |
| `unload()` | deregisters **all** entities; clears static prop batcher |

## Prop / actor resolve

- Props: `resolveLevelPropDefinition` → `instantiateProp` (engine spawn)
- Actors: `resolveLevelActorDefinition` → `actorDefinitionToSkeletalDef` → `spawnActor` + optional `createTestAi`

## Forbidden

- Reusing one Scene object across level ids — always create fresh via `useLevelScene`
- Kaykit-only `robots[]` / `dummies[]` arrays as the canonical level shape (legacy — migrated to indexed actors)
- Preloading entire `ACTOR_CATALOG` — walk the level index only
- Putting `aiPackage` / groups / `.level` parse under `viberanium/definitions`
- Construct importing sandbox or sandbox importing construct
